    overview: `Landmark Centre is a UFI-certified, 45,000+ square foot convention and event facility on Victoria Island, Lagos — hosting major international exhibitions (Propak West Africa, Nigeria Energy, Food & Beverage West Africa), concerts, weddings, and corporate conferences. It seats 2,000 theatre-style and 1,200 banquet, with a 1,000-vehicle parking facility.

The previous website was static and outdated. Every enquiry funnelled through a single generic contact form, with no way for event planners to see space configurations, check the event calendar, or submit a qualified brief. The marketing team had no ability to update content without developer involvement.

I was brought in to redesign and rebuild the site end-to-end, owning both design and Framer development.`,

    challenge: `Three problems needed to be solved simultaneously:

• Conversion friction — event planners visiting the site had high intent but no self-service path. They couldn\'t see available dates, compare hall configurations, or understand pricing tiers without making a phone call. Every extra step between landing and enquiry was a leak.

• Content stagnation — the old site required a developer for any update. The events calendar was perpetually outdated, which undermined credibility with professional event organisers who plan 3–6 months ahead.

• Scale communication — Landmark Centre competes with venues like Eko Convention Centre. The site needed to convey the sheer physical scale (9.4 acres, Atlantic Ocean views, 8 configurable spaces) in a way that photographs alone couldn\'t achieve.`,

    pullQuote: `A beautiful site that goes stale is worse than an ugly one that stays current.`,

    approach: [
      'Audited competitor venue sites across Lagos and internationally to identify conversion patterns — found that the best-performing event venue sites lead with space configuration tools, not hero videos',
