    outcome: `Shipped as the live Landmark Events website. The marketing team now manages content independently, keeping the events calendar current for the first time.

Enquiry quality improved measurably — planners now arrive with dates, guest counts, and space preferences pre-specified, reducing back-and-forth with the sales team. Inbound lead volume increased after launch as the structured enquiry form lowered the threshold for first contact. Events calendar is now updated weekly by the marketing team, no developer involvement required. Site serves as the primary digital touchpoint for event organisers considering the venue for exhibitions, conferences, and social events.

Built entirely in Framer — design, interaction, CMS, and deployment — demonstrating that a single designer-developer can ship a production-grade marketing site for a venue of this calibre.`,

